'''Yazeed Moein Hasan Abu Laila''' ({{langx|ar|يَزِيد مُعِين حَسَن أَبُو لَيْلَى}}; born 8 January 1993) is a Jordanian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Jordanian Pro League]] side [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
On 27 January 2023, Abu Laila joined [[Saudi First Division League]] club [[Al-Jabalain FC|Al-Jabalain]] on [[Loan (association football)|loan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الفيصلي يوافق على إعارة حارس المرمى أبو ليلى لفريق الجبلين السعودي |url=https://alghad.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%B5%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%85%D9%89-%D8%A3%D8%A8/}}</ref> On 3 July, Abu Laila renewed his loan with Al-Jabalain on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=أبو ليلى يجدد اعارته مع الجبلين .. ويشكر جماهير الفيصلي !! |url=https://www.al-mala3b.net/index.php?page=article&id=31570}}</ref>

On 14 July 2024, Abu Laila signed for [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein SC]].

==International career==
Abu Laila made his debut for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] on 1 June 2017 in a 1–0 defeat to [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] at [[Basra International Stadium]].<ref name="NFT"/>

He was a part of the called up squad that reached the final of the 2023 edition of the [[AFC Asian Cup|Asian Cup]], playing every match.

